Dumping the sort option from [exception1.php|https://gist.github.com/jmikola/200cb049598ce9f9b766#file-exception1-php] after a second Query construction results in its value being displayed as "&UNKNOWN:0", which indicates some corruption.

Lastly, it's possible to invoke a segfault by executing one of these queries (see [segfault.php|https://gist.github.com/jmikola/200cb049598ce9f9b766#file-segfault-php]).

[~derick]' BSON serialization document says [protected/private properties should be discarded|https://github.com/10gen-labs/mongo-hhvm-driver-prototype/blob/master/serialization.rst#objects]
{quote}
If an object is of any other class, without implementing any special interface, serialize as a BSON document. Keep only public properties, and ignore protected and private properties.
{quote}

Currently that is not the case:
{code:php}
<?php
class special {
  public $public = "public";
  protected $protected = "protected";
  private $private = "private";
}
$special = new Special;
$ret = MongoDB\BSON\toPHP(MongoDB\BSON\fromPHP($special))
var_dump($ret);
?>
{code}
{noformat}
object(stdClass)#2 (3) {
  ["public"]=>
  string(6) "public"
  ["protected"]=>
  string(9) "protected"
  ["private"]=>
  string(7) "private"
}
{noformat}

{noformat}
 [2015-09-20T18:51:35+00:00] PHONGO: DEBUG > Creating Manager, phongo-1.0.0beta1[beta] - mongoc-1.1.2, libbson-1.1.3
{noformat}

